- Pleasure.
- And these are your mechanics.

238
00:14:46,780 --> 00:14:51,299
They're reporting exclusively to you,
as per contract.

239
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:53,139
Pleasure. Do you wanna see the car?

240
00:14:53,140 --> 00:14:54,585
Sure.

241
00:14:56,620 --> 00:14:58,031
Hello.

242
00:15:03,060 --> 00:15:05,506
There she is. P160.

243
00:15:06,380 --> 00:15:08,906
- Same as Regazzoni's?
- Identical in every detail.

244
00:15:09,860 --> 00:15:11,350
How much does she weigh?

245
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:14,106
- 600 kilos.
- But that's crazy.

246
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:16,979
- Why so heavy?
- It's a V12 engine.

247
00:15:16,980 --> 00:15:20,179
That lump weighs 190K on its own.

248
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:22,179
Okay.

249
00:15:22,180 --> 00:15:24,539
What horsepower are you getting? 490?

250
00:15:24,540 --> 00:15:27,019
- No, no, 450.
- Well, it's not enough.

251
00:15:27,020 --> 00:15:28,499
It needs to be 500,

252
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:30,259
and the engine
needs to be 20 kilo lighter.

253
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:31,579
We already tried.

254
00:15:31,580 --> 00:15:32,857
- Tried what?
- Everything.

255
00:15:32,940 --> 00:15:34,499
We replaced the entire exhaust system.

256
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:37,788
- Barely made a difference.
- Are you using magnesium parts?

257
00:15:50,820 --> 00:15:52,339
Now the engine block.

258
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:55,071
Any mounting or fixing plates,
strip it out also.

259
00:15:55,380 --> 00:15:58,539
When you've done that,
we have to look at the aerodynamics,

260
00:15:58,540 --> 00:16:00,304
front and rear wing.

261
00:16:17,740 --> 00:16:19,822
Okay, thank you. Good night.

262
00:16:39,780 --> 00:16:41,225
What was Regazzoni's time?

263
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:44,511
1:53.

264
00:16:44,860 --> 00:16:47,779
Okay, now put him in my car,
and he'll go round two seconds faster.

265
00:16:47,780 --> 00:16:50,829
- Well, that's impossible.
- No chance.

266
00:16:53,860 --> 00:16:56,219
We've been working on it all night.

267
00:16:56,220 --> 00:16:58,339
Put Regazzoni in the car.
See what happens.

268
00:16:58,340 --> 00:17:00,259
I don't understand.
Why am I supposed to do this?

269
00:17:00,260 --> 00:17:03,210
I don't know, Clay.
He just wants you to take it for a spin.

270
00:17:05,460 --> 00:17:07,059
Gloves, please.

271
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:08,505
<i>'fanculo.</i>

272
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:54,819
- I would say we push it a bit...
- All right.

273
00:17:54,820 --> 00:17:56,899
What did you do to the car?

274
00:17:56,900 --> 00:18:00,427
That's information I will share with you
under certain conditions only.

275
00:18:00,660 --> 00:18:02,105
Go on.

276
00:18:03,180 --> 00:18:04,864
A guaranteed place in the team,

277
00:18:05,220 --> 00:18:08,370
and a paid contract on equal terms
with Regazzoni for two years.

278
00:18:08,980 --> 00:18:10,584
Are you crazy?

279
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:14,227
Clay's a senior figure in Formula 1.
You're just a rookie.

280
00:18:14,580 --> 00:18:17,337
Well, the only reason we took you on
is because you're paying us.

281
00:18:17,420 --> 00:18:20,739
Well, as of now, if you want me to stay,
we rip up the contract.

282
00:18:20,740 --> 00:18:23,471
- I don't pay you a cent.
- That's outrageous!

283
00:18:23,980 --> 00:18:26,062
Was he quicker in my car?

284
00:18:26,780 --> 00:18:28,782
He was, wasn't he?

285
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,741
Did he go two seconds faster?

286
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:36,825
2.3.

287
00:18:39,540 --> 00:18:41,668
So, have a think,

288
00:18:42,300 --> 00:18:44,541
work out your priorities
and get back to me.

289
00:18:59,540 --> 00:19:00,951
Hey, Niki.

290
00:19:03,340 --> 00:19:06,257
I know what you're going to say,
that it's none of my business.

291
00:19:06,340 --> 00:19:07,341
What?

292
00:19:08,740 --> 00:19:12,062
If it's the track manager
you're taking on your date tonight...

293
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:14,739
It's none of your business.

294
00:19:14,740 --> 00:19:18,506
Okay, but if you want my advice,
I'd let this one go.

295
00:19:19,860 --> 00:19:23,501
I'm not questioning your taste.
She is a great girl, but...

296
00:19:25,140 --> 00:19:29,099
Agnes's last boyfriend
was a British Formula 2 driver

297
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:31,499
who has a reputation for two things.

298
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:34,185
For being a little crazy on the track,

299
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:38,504
and for going all night and all day
and all night again in bed.

300
00:19:38,620 --> 00:19:42,139
He's a good driver,
but an immortal fuck, apparently.

301
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:45,340
I don't know about you, but
that's not an act I'd like to follow.

302
00:19:48,420 --> 00:19:50,502
But if that doesn't bother you...

303
00:19:52,420 --> 00:19:55,390
What's his name, the driver?

304
00:19:55,620 --> 00:19:57,145
Hunt. James Hunt.

305
00:20:01,260 --> 00:20:04,707
You see, you share information
and I share information.

306
00:20:06,060 --> 00:20:08,267
That's what teammates are for.

307
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:20,059
<i>Where the hell are we going?</i>

308
00:20:20,060 --> 00:20:22,419
<i>I promise it'll be worth it.</i>

309
00:20:22,420 --> 00:20:23,865
<i>Just keep them closed.</i>

310
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:25,745
Wait for it.

311
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:28,389
Wait for it.

312
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:34,186
There. What do you say?

313
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,870
She's Formula 1.

314
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,984
Yes, she is, Superstar.

315
00:20:38,420 --> 00:20:41,299
Your brother and I got together
with the bean counters.

316
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,779
And since the economics of F1

317
00:20:42,780 --> 00:20:46,419
are not so significantly different
to the economics of Formula 2,

318
00:20:46,420 --> 00:20:48,857
well, we thought if we were
going to be losing money,

319
00:20:48,940 --> 00:20:52,059
we might as well be doing it on
the big roulette table in Formula 1.

320
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:55,382
You fat, little, inbred beauty.
Come here.

321
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:03,022
Actually, credit where it's due,
we got the idea from Niki.

322
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:05,299
- Who?
- Lauda.

323
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:08,139
Bought his way in, rather than
mess about in the lower divisions.

324
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:09,857
I thought, "Bloody hell, he's right."

325
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:13,419
No sponsorship, Superstar.
I hope you approve.

326
00:21:13,420 --> 00:21:17,425
No vulgar logos for cigarettes or condoms.

327
00:21:17,980 --> 00:21:20,028
Just plain white with the flags. Ooh!

328
00:21:20,460 --> 00:21:23,430
And racing overalls which read,

329
00:21:24,620 --> 00:21:27,219
"Sex. Breakfast of champions."

330
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:31,709
So, when do we start?

331
00:21:32,660 --> 00:21:34,867
- Soon as you're ready.
- Ready?

332
00:21:35,180 --> 00:21:37,751
I've been waiting for this my whole life.

333
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:48,779
- Hi, welcome to Watkins Glen.
- Hello!

334
00:21:48,780 --> 00:21:50,777
<i>When the season started, people wondered</i>

335
00:21:50,860 --> 00:21:53,810
<i>whether Lord Hesketh and his team
of upper-class enthusiasts</i>

336
00:21:54,020 --> 00:21:58,499
<i>were bringing glamour
to the racing community, or just comedy.</i>

337
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:00,659
Certainly, it was the first time
anyone had seen

338
00:22:00,660 --> 00:22:04,299
a butler serving oysters and caviar
in the pits.

339
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:07,139
But they have made quite an impact.

340
00:22:07,140 --> 00:22:10,379
Sixth in France, fourth in Britain
and third in Holland.

341
00:22:10,380 --> 00:22:14,059
<i>All drivers on the track,
caution flags are out.</i>

342
00:22:14,060 --> 00:22:16,234
<i>A severe crash at the Esses.</i>

343
00:22:16,235 --> 00:22:18,339
<i>Red flag.
There is a car off the track.</i>

344
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:20,099
And reports are reaching me

345
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:22,431
that there has been
a serious accident in qualifying.

346
00:22:22,514 --> 00:22:25,259
Er, the identity of the driver we don't
currently have at the moment,

347
00:22:25,260 --> 00:22:27,467
but, as you can tell from all the activity

348
00:22:27,580 --> 00:22:29,259
going on behind me towards the track,

349
00:22:29,260 --> 00:22:31,739
it is clearly a grave incident indeed.

350
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:33,219
We will, of course,
have more information for you

351
00:22:33,220 --> 00:22:34,297
as and when we get it,

352
00:22:34,380 --> 00:22:38,385
but it is the sight and sound
of Formula 1 nobody likes to see.

353
00:22:42,380 --> 00:22:44,330
- Get your hands off me.
- Hey, come on.

354
00:22:54,075 --> 00:22:55,739
<i>Drivers of top stature</i>

355
00:22:55,740 --> 00:22:57,539
<i>we've lost just in the past four seasons</i>

356
00:22:57,540 --> 00:23:02,459
<i>have included Piers Courage, Jochen Rindt,</i>

357
00:23:02,460 --> 00:23:05,819
<i>Jo Siffert, Roger Williamson</i>

358
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:08,099
<i>and today, at Watkins Glen,</i>

359
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:10,421
<i>Formula 1 has claimed another driver.</i>

360
00:23:11,020 --> 00:23:13,307
<i>The Tyrrell team
have withdrawn from the race.</i>

361
00:23:13,420 --> 00:23:16,139
<i>Their places on the grid
will be left empty.</i>

362
00:23:16,140 --> 00:23:18,586
- Terrible.
- They should cancel the race.

363
00:23:18,820 --> 00:23:20,345
Why?

364
00:23:20,660 --> 00:23:23,106
He made a mistake,
went into the corner too fast.

365
00:23:23,220 --> 00:23:24,699
It's his fault.

366
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:26,589
- Is that right?
- It's obvious.

367
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:28,709
Look at the tyre marks.

368
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:32,419
So says the nobody
who had to pay for his own drive.

369
00:23:32,420 --> 00:23:34,217
How's that working out for you,
by the way?

370
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:37,110
Fine. How is it at the back?

371
00:23:38,020 --> 00:23:40,102
Not planning on being there for long.

372
00:23:40,875 --> 00:23:42,579
<i>Ten minutes to the warm-up lap.</i>

373
00:23:42,580 --> 00:23:44,099
<i>Ten minutes.</i>

374
00:23:44,100 --> 00:23:45,431
<i>Asshole.</i>

375
00:23:47,420 --> 00:23:48,785
Arsehole.

376
00:23:50,180 --> 00:23:53,539
<i>Heading into
the Grand Hotel hairpin, second gear.</i>

377
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:54,619
Turn in hard,

378
00:23:54,620 --> 00:23:57,271
looking for late apex,
gentle with the bar.

379
00:23:59,020 --> 00:24:02,149
Heading into Portier, second gear,
clip the apex,

380
00:24:02,260 --> 00:24:05,821
light brake, stay in second,
looking for a good exit.

381
00:24:06,180 --> 00:24:08,299
Heading through the tunnel, gradual right,

382
00:24:08,300 --> 00:24:11,339
up through third, fourth, fifth...

383
00:24:11,340 --> 00:24:13,342
Is Alexander round?

384
00:24:13,860 --> 00:24:16,539
Er, yes, he was.

385
00:24:16,540 --> 00:24:18,219
He went back to the house to take a call.

386
00:24:18,220 --> 00:24:20,059
He'll be back shortly.

387
00:24:20,060 --> 00:24:22,222
He only wanted to show me
his pride and joy.

388
00:24:23,180 --> 00:24:25,979
Rhymes with "boy", if you ask me.

389
00:24:25,980 --> 00:24:27,859
And "toy".

390
00:24:27,860 --> 00:24:32,139
God, it's so flimsy
for something that costs so much.

391
00:24:32,140 --> 00:24:36,219
There's no comfort,
no protection, nothing.

392
00:24:36,220 --> 00:24:38,939
No, it's just a little coffin, really.

393
00:24:38,940 --> 00:24:42,059
Surrounded by high-octane fuel in here.

394
00:24:42,060 --> 00:24:45,059
Being driven round 170 miles per hour.

395
00:24:45,060 --> 00:24:48,223
To all intents and purposes,
this thing's a bomb on wheels.

396
00:24:49,380 --> 00:24:51,303
You're James, aren't you?

397
00:24:52,540 --> 00:24:54,030
Yes.

398
00:24:54,980 --> 00:24:56,709
You fit the description.

399
00:24:57,100 --> 00:24:58,511
Is that right?

400
00:24:59,740 --> 00:25:01,708
Suzy. Friend of Alex's.

401
00:25:01,820 --> 00:25:04,949
Yeah, yeah. I know exactly.

402
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:08,179
What was the description?

403
00:25:08,180 --> 00:25:09,779
Mostly positive, in terms of appearance.

404
00:25:09,780 --> 00:25:11,987
Negative only in terms of character.

405
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:14,423
I've been told to avoid you.

406
00:25:14,820 --> 00:25:16,231
By whom?

407
00:25:16,660 --> 00:25:19,579
Alexander. He says you're a bad boy.

408
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:21,939
Alexander doesn't know
what he's talking about.

409
00:25:21,940 --> 00:25:24,379
I was. I'm not any more.

410
00:25:24,380 --> 00:25:27,979
The new me is very professional.
Early to bed, early to rise.

411
00:25:27,980 --> 00:25:29,619
- All very dull.
- Hmm.

412
00:25:29,620 --> 00:25:31,059
But according to the team,

413
00:25:31,060 --> 00:25:33,741
"The best way to
keep beating the goose-stepper."

414
00:25:34,435 --> 00:25:36,139
Is that what you were doing
when I came in?

415
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:39,179
Yes, visualisation techniques,
memorising the circuit,

416
00:25:39,180 --> 00:25:41,865
in this case Monaco, which is up next.

417
00:25:46,660 --> 00:25:49,899
Personally, I've always been a great
believer in getting there on the day,

418
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:52,850
putting my foot down
and playing chicken with everyone else.

419
00:25:54,515 --> 00:25:56,219
But they don't want me
doing that any more.

420
00:25:56,220 --> 00:26:00,305
They want my body like a temple
and my mind like a monk.

421
00:26:00,980 --> 00:26:04,179
And what about your soul, your heart?

422
00:26:04,180 --> 00:26:06,419
Well, they've got ideas about that, too.

423
00:26:06,420 --> 00:26:09,019
They want me to stop messing around,
settle down,

424
00:26:09,020 --> 00:26:11,339
get married
with the next nice girl I meet.

425
00:26:11,340 --> 00:26:13,090
They think it would be good for me.

426
00:26:13,220 --> 00:26:15,222
Hmm. What do you think?

427
00:26:15,580 --> 00:26:18,902
It sounds fucking awful.

428
00:26:20,020 --> 00:26:22,387
But since they're right about most things,

429
00:26:22,660 --> 00:26:25,379
- they're probably right about that, too.
- Hmm.

430
00:26:25,380 --> 00:26:27,781
You don't fancy getting married, do you?

431
00:26:53,180 --> 00:26:54,705
Suzy.

432
00:26:55,420 --> 00:26:56,831
Bravo!

433
00:26:57,180 --> 00:26:59,103
Hey, hey, hey!

434
00:27:02,660 --> 00:27:04,857
- What's going on with him?
- Nothing. Nothing.

435
00:27:04,940 --> 00:27:06,390
Didn't want to ruin your day.

436
00:27:06,940 --> 00:27:09,341
It's... It's the Kraut.

437
00:27:09,620 --> 00:27:11,190
What about him?

438
00:27:12,060 --> 00:27:13,979
He's just been signed by Ferrari.

439
00:27:13,980 --> 00:27:17,701
You're kidding me?
Jesus. How did that happen?

440
00:27:17,980 --> 00:27:19,497
Did he buy his way in there, too?

441
00:27:19,580 --> 00:27:25,219
Well, the old man took Regazzoni back
and he insisted on it, apparently.

442
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:27,620
He says that Niki's a genius
setting up the cars.

443
00:27:46,500 --> 00:27:48,264
It's terrible. Drives like a pig.

444
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:51,467
- Oh, you can't say that.
- Why not?

445
00:27:51,820 --> 00:27:53,868
- It's a Ferrari!
- It's a shitbox.

446
00:27:54,340 --> 00:27:57,779
It understeers like crazy and
the weight distribution is a disaster.

447
00:27:57,780 --> 00:28:01,430
It's amazing, all these facilities
and you make a piece of crap like this.

448
00:28:02,220 --> 00:28:03,659
Uh!

449
00:28:10,897 --> 00:28:14,897
We are happy
to welcome back to the Ferrari family...

450
00:28:15,237 --> 00:28:17,357
our good friend Clay Regazzoni,

451
00:28:17,737 --> 00:28:19,777
and to introduce Niki Lauda,

452
00:28:20,407 --> 00:28:21,487
from Austria.

453
00:28:32,300 --> 00:28:35,539
"Ferrari family."
"Our good friend Clay Regazzoni."

454
00:28:35,540 --> 00:28:39,099
You are family and friend
to the commendatore as long as you win.

455
00:28:39,100 --> 00:28:40,737
The minute you don't, ciao, ciao.

456
00:28:40,820 --> 00:28:44,950
I totally understand. It's business.
I would do the same.

457
00:28:45,060 --> 00:28:48,059
But it isn't
just business, is it? What we do.

458
00:28:48,060 --> 00:28:50,219
It's passion, love.

459
00:28:50,220 --> 00:28:53,059
Which is why we are prepared
to risk our lives for it.

460
00:28:53,060 --> 00:28:54,179
Not me.

461
00:28:54,180 --> 00:28:56,977
If I had more talent and could earn
better money with something else,

462
00:28:57,060 --> 00:28:58,739
I would.

463
00:28:58,740 --> 00:29:02,419
How do you know you will
make money here? You haven't yet.

464
00:29:02,420 --> 00:29:04,741
Not yet, but I will.

465
00:29:05,420 --> 00:29:07,309
If you can, I can.

466
00:29:11,180 --> 00:29:13,080
You know, are you ever not an asshole?

467
00:29:14,380 --> 00:29:16,419
- Why am I an asshole?
- Well...

468
00:29:16,420 --> 00:29:18,019
You know, by now I'm both quicker than you

469
00:29:18,020 --> 00:29:19,939
and better at setting up the car.

470
00:29:19,940 --> 00:29:21,779
You can't deal with it,
so you're the asshole.

471
00:29:21,780 --> 00:29:22,941
Screw you.

472
00:29:30,860 --> 00:29:34,139
I brought you along today because
you seem like a lonely kind of guy.

473
00:29:34,140 --> 00:29:36,099
I thought if I introduced you
to some nice people,

474
00:29:36,100 --> 00:29:37,979
that could rub off on you.

475
00:29:37,980 --> 00:29:40,699
Forget it. Make your own friends.

476
00:29:40,700 --> 00:29:43,385
Come on, Clay. I'm sorry.

477
00:30:18,900 --> 00:30:20,345
Are you leaving?

478
00:30:21,460 --> 00:30:22,871
Yes.

479
00:30:23,340 --> 00:30:25,099
Can you give me a lift
to the nearest town,

480
00:30:25,100 --> 00:30:26,600
anywhere with a train station?

481
00:30:28,340 --> 00:30:31,423
Sure. Trento's half an hour's drive.

482
00:30:32,060 --> 00:30:33,107
Get in.

483
00:30:44,460 --> 00:30:47,907
<i>Been another blue day without you, girl</i>

484
