You wanna change?

963
01:05:56,860 --> 01:05:59,419
- Is Niki gonna change?
- No.

964
01:05:59,420 --> 01:06:01,502
Then we stay on wets, too.

965
01:06:09,340 --> 01:06:11,104
- Niki, okay?
- I'm good.

966
01:06:13,580 --> 01:06:16,060
All right, fire her up.

967
01:06:29,274 --> 01:06:32,059
<i>This season's fight for
the Formula 1 World Championship</i>

968
01:06:32,060 --> 01:06:35,739
<i>has so far been the story of two men.</i>

969
01:06:35,740 --> 01:06:39,419
<i>Thus far, it's been going
pretty much the way of Niki Lauda.</i>

970
01:06:39,420 --> 01:06:42,105
<i>But James Hunt has qualified fastest here.</i>

971
01:06:42,220 --> 01:06:45,299
<i>He is on pole position
for the German Grand Prix,</i>

972
01:06:45,300 --> 01:06:48,383
<i>with Niki Lauda alongside
in the blood-red Ferrari.</i>

973
01:06:49,820 --> 01:06:51,299
<i>It's a long race.</i>

974
01:06:51,300 --> 01:06:53,951
If the track starts to dry out,

975
01:06:54,060 --> 01:06:56,904
the wet-weather tyres
will no longer be as quick.

976
01:07:18,315 --> 01:07:20,419
Niki Lauda and James Hunt, side by side

977
01:07:20,420 --> 01:07:23,583
on the front row of the grid,
go away absolutely as one.

978
01:07:37,780 --> 01:07:39,987
<i>Lauda very aggressive on Hunt there,</i>

979
01:07:40,100 --> 01:07:42,102
<i>forcing the McLaren onto the grass.</i>

980
01:07:46,460 --> 01:07:47,939
<i>Lauda has the lead at the moment.</i>

981
01:07:47,940 --> 01:07:50,307
Lauda leads into the first corner.

982
01:07:50,500 --> 01:07:52,468
<i>Hunt is in second place.</i>

983
01:07:57,140 --> 01:07:59,779
<i>Mass storming past Hunt!</i>

984
01:07:59,780 --> 01:08:02,630
<i>He made the right choice
to go with the dry-weather tyres.</i>

985
01:08:03,980 --> 01:08:05,789
<i>Mass passing Lauda now!</i>

986
01:08:05,900 --> 01:08:09,825
<i>Jochen Mass, in the number 12 McLaren,
takes the lead!</i>

987
01:08:09,980 --> 01:08:11,664
Jochen Mass the clear leader,

988
01:08:11,820 --> 01:08:13,868
with everybody else making the decision

989
01:08:13,980 --> 01:08:16,139
to change tyres
after just one lap of this race.

990
01:08:16,140 --> 01:08:18,347
He's coming in! Come on, let's go!

991
01:08:26,500 --> 01:08:30,550
See? I told you to go on slicks.
You should have taken my advice.

992
01:08:30,660 --> 01:08:32,499
Fuck off. Where's Niki?

993
01:08:32,500 --> 01:08:35,185
Behind you.
He made the same mistake.

994
01:08:47,940 --> 01:08:49,669
Come on!

995
01:08:52,220 --> 01:08:54,029
Come on! What's going on?

996
01:08:55,540 --> 01:08:58,899
The tyre-changing frenzy has caused
a huge reshuffling of the pack,

997
01:08:58,900 --> 01:09:01,870
- with Jochen Mass in the lead now.
- You're clear. Go!

998
01:09:02,420 --> 01:09:03,546
Quick!

999
01:09:05,020 --> 01:09:06,859
Lauda urging his mechanics to hurry.

1000
01:09:06,860 --> 01:09:08,160
Quicker, quicker, quicker!

1001
01:09:09,780 --> 01:09:11,862
It's a disaster! Come on!

1002
01:09:23,420 --> 01:09:24,990
What's going on, you assholes?

1003
01:09:48,740 --> 01:09:50,979
This race has gone wrong for him so far.

1004
01:09:50,980 --> 01:09:54,427
<i>His championship rival, James Hunt,
is a long way up the road.</i>

1005
01:10:05,300 --> 01:10:06,779
<i>Lauda passing car after car.</i>

1006
01:10:06,780 --> 01:10:10,262
<i>He's just going past
Mario Andretti's Lotus there.</i>

1007
01:10:56,980 --> 01:10:58,982
Niki!

1008
01:11:03,980 --> 01:11:06,062
Get me out! Help me!

1009
01:11:06,660 --> 01:11:09,260
<i>We have an accident
on the course. Red flags are out.</i>

1010
01:11:09,500 --> 01:11:13,300
<i>Several cars are involved. Looks like
it might be one of the Ferraris.</i>

1011
01:11:20,500 --> 01:11:22,867
- Come this way.
- Come on, come on!

1012
01:11:35,100 --> 01:11:36,579
Keep trying.

1013
01:11:44,180 --> 01:11:45,820
- Come this way.
- Okay.

1014
01:11:51,557 --> 01:11:58,187
<i>News is reaching us that Niki Lauda
was involved in the accident.</i>

1015
01:11:58,267 --> 01:12:04,237
<i>He is being flown by helicopter
to Mannheim hospital with severe burns.</i>

1016
01:12:37,740 --> 01:12:41,790
<i>It's not
the burns to his face that are the danger.</i>

1017
01:12:42,857 --> 01:12:44,857
<i>It's the burns to his lungs.</i>

1018
01:12:47,607 --> 01:12:49,834
In the intensive care unit,

1019
01:12:49,835 --> 01:12:52,891
six doctors and thirty-four
nurses are on duty for him.

1020
01:12:54,077 --> 01:12:57,367
But his condition is far worse
than originally feared.

1021
01:13:24,100 --> 01:13:27,619
<i>The flood, which swept
down Big Thompson Canyon in Colorado,</i>

1022
01:13:27,620 --> 01:13:29,339
<i>was the worst since records began.</i>

1023
01:13:29,340 --> 01:13:31,939
<i>In Formula 1 today,
victory celebrations were muted</i>

1024
01:13:31,940 --> 01:13:35,779
<i>after a horrific accident involving
world champion Niki Lauda.</i>

1025
01:13:35,780 --> 01:13:37,779
<i>Due to safety concerns before the race,</i>

1026
01:13:37,780 --> 01:13:40,179
<i>the Austrian had said
he would not take part,</i>

1027
01:13:40,180 --> 01:13:41,670
<i>but in the end he did.</i>

1028
01:13:43,060 --> 01:13:45,377
<i>He was making up for lost time
when he went off the track,</i>

1029
01:13:45,460 --> 01:13:47,827
<i>puncturing the Ferrari's fuel tank.</i>

1030
01:13:48,220 --> 01:13:50,577
<i>Brett Lunger was unable to
avoid the flaming wreck,</i>

1031
01:13:50,660 --> 01:13:53,659
<i>but was unhurt and joined with
the other drivers to rescue Lauda,</i>

1032
01:13:53,660 --> 01:13:56,550
<i>who was taken to Mannheim Hospital
with severe burns,</i>

1033
01:13:56,660 --> 01:14:00,301
<i>the incident reminding us again
of the dangers of Formula 1.</i>

1034
01:14:00,420 --> 01:14:02,499
<i>Niki Lauda was trapped for almost a minute</i>

1035
01:14:02,500 --> 01:14:05,151
<i>in a searing inferno of 800-plus degrees.</i>

1036
01:14:13,980 --> 01:14:16,259
- Do we have any change this morning?
- No...

1037
01:14:16,260 --> 01:14:18,183
<i>Frau</i> Lauda. <i>Frau</i> Lauda?

1038
01:14:19,020 --> 01:14:21,182
He's awake and just spoke.

1039
01:14:22,787 --> 01:14:26,377
He said, "Tell the priest to fuck off!
I'm still alive!"

1040
01:14:26,547 --> 01:14:28,207
You can go in.

1041
01:15:49,957 --> 01:15:54,547
<i>James Hunt gains on the absent Niki Lauda.</i>

1042
01:16:01,717 --> 01:16:03,787
<i>We need to vacuum the lungs.</i>

1043
01:16:04,566 --> 01:16:07,260
<i>I should warn you. It won't be easy.</i>

1044
01:17:16,337 --> 01:17:17,717
Do it again.

1045
01:17:17,967 --> 01:17:22,121
Are you sure?
The lungs will already be bruised.

1046
01:17:53,140 --> 01:17:54,904
- Niki...

1047
01:18:04,047 --> 01:18:06,137
Please, stop.

1048
01:18:07,137 --> 01:18:10,687
I know what you're thinking, but please...

1049
01:18:12,017 --> 01:18:15,317
If you love me, you won't say a word.

1050
01:18:51,940 --> 01:18:53,890
- Morning, chaps.
- Hey, here's the man.

1051
01:18:54,020 --> 01:18:55,670
Looking good.

1052
01:18:58,900 --> 01:19:01,779
- What's going on?
- Jesus. It's Niki.

1053
01:19:01,780 --> 01:19:03,828
- What about him?
- He's here.

1054
01:19:04,140 --> 01:19:05,665
- What?
- He's racing.

1055
01:19:21,020 --> 01:19:22,670
Niki.

1056
01:19:29,300 --> 01:19:30,825
It's that bad, huh?

1057
01:19:32,140 --> 01:19:33,551
No.

1058
01:19:34,420 --> 01:19:37,419
In hospital I asked them straight,
no bullshit,

1059
01:19:37,420 --> 01:19:39,263
how bad my appearance would be.

1060
01:19:40,500 --> 01:19:42,867
They said with time it would be fine.

1061
01:19:43,740 --> 01:19:45,344
But it won't.

1062
01:19:46,260 --> 01:19:49,104
I can tell, seeing your reaction.

1063
01:19:50,060 --> 01:19:53,360
I will spend the rest of my life
with a face that frightens people.

1064
01:19:57,180 --> 01:20:00,946
You know, Niki, I tried to write you
a letter at the time, to apologise.

1065
01:20:02,580 --> 01:20:05,060
The drivers' meeting in Germany,
before the race.

1066
01:20:05,180 --> 01:20:07,706
- I swayed the room.
- Yes, you did.

1067
01:20:07,900 --> 01:20:10,107
That race should never have gone ahead.

1068
01:20:10,860 --> 01:20:12,464
No, it shouldn't.

1069
01:20:12,900 --> 01:20:16,619
So, in many ways, I feel responsible
for what happened, and...

1070
01:20:16,620 --> 01:20:18,190
You were.

1071
01:20:19,860 --> 01:20:21,589
But, trust me...

1072
01:20:22,740 --> 01:20:26,790
watching you win those races
while I was fighting for my life...

1073
01:20:29,100 --> 01:20:32,309
...you were equally responsible
for getting me back in the car.

1074
01:21:00,060 --> 01:21:02,745
- How are you feeling, Niki?
- Fine.

1075
01:21:03,140 --> 01:21:06,779
Niki, can you confirm to us exactly
which procedures you've had

1076
01:21:06,780 --> 01:21:08,782
and the expectations for your recovery?

1077
01:21:09,340 --> 01:21:10,785
Sure.

1078
01:21:10,940 --> 01:21:12,779
I had a skin graft operation,

1079
01:21:12,780 --> 01:21:15,101
where they put half my right thigh
in my face.

1080
01:21:17,300 --> 01:21:22,139
Now, it doesn't look too good,
but one unexpected advantage is

1081
01:21:22,140 --> 01:21:24,499
it's impossible to perspire
through a skin graft,

1082
01:21:24,500 --> 01:21:28,000
so sweat will never run into my eyes
again, which is good for a driver.

1083
01:21:30,140 --> 01:21:31,819
When they heard about your condition,

1084
01:21:31,820 --> 01:21:35,267
Ferrari immediately hired
a replacement driver, Carlos Reutemann.

1085
01:21:35,940 --> 01:21:39,979
Yeah, before even reaching the hospital.

1086
01:21:39,980 --> 01:21:42,028
Is Reutemann driving today, too?

1087
01:21:42,460 --> 01:21:45,464
Yes, and keen to make an impression.

1088
01:21:45,660 --> 01:21:49,659
So, let's see where Mr Reutemann
finishes and where I finish today.

1089
01:21:51,180 --> 01:21:54,330
James Hunt and McLaren have
caught up a lot while you were away.

1090
01:21:54,500 --> 01:21:55,990
Yes.

1091
01:21:56,620 --> 01:21:59,870
So is there a question now,
or are you just trying to piss me off?

1092
01:22:02,900 --> 01:22:04,629
You still think you can win?

1093
01:22:05,060 --> 01:22:06,859
Yes, of course.

1094
01:22:06,860 --> 01:22:08,862
I have the better car.

1095
01:22:08,980 --> 01:22:11,460
And possibly I'm the better driver.

1096
01:22:11,660 --> 01:22:14,139
But he's a clever guy,
and he's used his time well

1097
01:22:14,140 --> 01:22:18,190
while I was lying half-dead in hospital
to win some points.

1098
01:22:20,140 --> 01:22:22,825
And what did your wife say
when she saw your face?

1099
01:22:29,020 --> 01:22:32,579
She said, "Sweetie,
you don't need a face to drive."

1100
01:22:32,580 --> 01:22:34,708
"You just need a right foot."

1101
01:22:35,020 --> 01:22:37,387
I'm being serious.

1102
01:22:37,580 --> 01:22:42,063
Do you really think your marriage can
survive with the way you look now?

1103
01:22:44,700 --> 01:22:46,748
And I'm being serious, too.

1104
01:22:47,740 --> 01:22:50,710
Fuck you. Press conference over.

1105
01:22:55,395 --> 01:22:57,739
- That was hairy.
- Well, you got noticed, Clive.

1106
01:22:57,740 --> 01:22:59,099
I'll tell you that.

1107
01:22:59,100 --> 01:23:00,779
I thought it went well, to be honest.

1108
01:23:00,780 --> 01:23:02,579
They don't like it
when it's not going their way.

1109
01:23:02,580 --> 01:23:04,264
- Clive.
- That's the game.

1110
01:23:04,380 --> 01:23:06,699
- See you.
- See you later.

1111
01:23:06,700 --> 01:23:08,617
- James, are you all right?
- Good, yeah.

1112
01:23:08,700 --> 01:23:10,459
Listen, I think I've got something for you

1113
01:23:10,460 --> 01:23:12,259
on that last question, about Niki.

1114
01:23:12,260 --> 01:23:14,866
You heard about that?
I did.

1115
01:23:16,100 --> 01:23:17,829
James.

1116
01:23:24,060 --> 01:23:26,631
Please, James...

1117
01:23:27,620 --> 01:23:30,544
Now go home to your wife
and ask her how you look.

1118
01:23:32,980 --> 01:23:34,391
Prick.

1119
01:23:51,260 --> 01:23:56,141
So Niki Lauda, just 42 days after
his near-fatal accident at Nürburgring,

1120
01:23:56,260 --> 01:23:57,819
will race here today at Monza

1121
01:23:57,820 --> 01:24:01,586
against all medical advice
and no doubt in incredible pain.

1122
01:24:34,300 --> 01:24:36,019
<i>...Niki Lauda!</i>

1123
01:24:44,660 --> 01:24:47,061
<i>Photographers, please clear the grid.</i>

1124
01:24:47,300 --> 01:24:49,462
Niki, it's time.

1125
01:24:50,980 --> 01:24:52,470
Okay?

1126
01:24:59,140 --> 01:25:00,551
<i>Please clear the grid.</i>

1127
01:25:03,180 --> 01:25:05,308
<i>One minute to go.</i>

1128
01:25:42,637 --> 01:25:46,347
That's a bad start for Lauda,
he's slow away.

1129
01:25:51,100 --> 01:25:54,019
<i>The returning Niki Lauda
seems overwhelmed.</i>

1130
01:25:54,020 --> 01:25:56,466
<i>He's being overtaken by car after car.</i>

1131
01:25:59,300 --> 01:26:01,026
A terrible start for the Austrian.

1132
01:26:01,027 --> 01:26:03,427
<i>It's perhaps too soon for him
to be racing again.</i>

1133
01:26:06,260 --> 01:26:09,389
<i>Lauda's off line.
He runs wide onto the grass.</i>

1134
01:26:14,220 --> 01:26:15,970
<i>He wrestles it back onto the track,</i>

1135
01:26:16,100 --> 01:26:18,910
<i>but that was a bad moment for Niki.</i>

1136
01:26:22,780 --> 01:26:25,059
<i>Niki Lauda's the reigning world champion,</i>

1137
01:26:25,060 --> 01:26:28,269
<i>but maybe in his current state
he's a danger out there,</i>

1138
01:26:28,420 --> 01:26:31,230
<i>to himself and to the rest of the field.</i>

1139
01:26:33,220 --> 01:26:37,111
<i>And Stuck has collided
with Mario Andretti's Lotus!</i>

1140
01:26:37,260 --> 01:26:40,423
<i>Niki's boxed in. He's got nowhere to go.</i>

1141
01:26:54,860 --> 01:26:58,421
<i>Niki Lauda is actually
making a move. He's on Brambilla's tail.</i>

1142
01:27:01,700 --> 01:27:04,351
<i>He pulls out of the slipstream
to overtake.</i>

1143
01:27:05,100 --> 01:27:07,421
<i>Lauda's starting to find the form</i>

1144
01:27:07,540 --> 01:27:09,890
<i>that, early in this race,
we believed he'd lost.</i>

1145
01:27:15,940 --> 01:27:20,025
Lauda's now lapping faster than
Reutemann and closing the gap ahead.

1146
01:27:23,940 --> 01:27:26,511
<i>Lauda closing on Carlos Reutemann,</i>

1147
01:27:26,620 --> 01:27:29,783
<i>the man called in to be his replacement
in the Ferrari team.</i>

1148
01:27:38,820 --> 01:27:40,629
<i>And there's James Hunt's McLaren,</i>

1149
01:27:40,740 --> 01:27:43,186
<i>smoking stationary
by the side of the road.</i>

1150
01:27:46,820 --> 01:27:49,903
<i>This is bad news for Hunt's
championship hopes.</i>

1151
01:27:54,300 --> 01:27:55,711
<i>It's Ronnie Peterson</i>

1152
01:27:55,820 --> 01:27:58,187
<i>who comes home the winner here at Monza.</i>

1153
01:27:58,380 --> 01:28:01,330
<i>But all eyes are on the man
who finishes a brilliant fourth,</i>

1154
01:28:02,220 --> 01:28:04,348
<i>Niki Lauda!</i>

1155
01:28:45,220 --> 01:28:47,619
<i>What a race, what a man, what a season.</i>

1156
01:28:47,620 --> 01:28:49,859
With a fourth-place finish
and three priceless points,

1157
01:28:49,860 --> 01:28:51,899
it means that Niki Lauda
is a major step closer

1158
01:28:51,900 --> 01:28:54,107
to retaining the World Championship.

1159
01:29:53,260 --> 01:29:56,819
<i>So, the long, gruelling
and incredibly dramatic season</i>

1160
01:29:56,820 --> 01:29:59,259
<i>comes down to this final race in Japan</i>

1161
01:29:59,260 --> 01:30:01,859
<i>in the shadow of Mount Fuji.</i>

1162
01:30:01,860 --> 01:30:03,339
<i>Niki Lauda goes into</i>

1163
01:30:03,340 --> 01:30:04,859
<i>this deciding race at Fuji</i>

1164
01:30:04,860 --> 01:30:07,099
<i>just three points ahead of James Hunt.</i>

1165
01:30:07,100 --> 01:30:11,389
<i>Hunt knowing he must beat the Austrian
fair and square to take the title.</i>

1166
01:30:12,940 --> 01:30:16,499
James, do you think
you can cope with the pressure?

1167
01:30:16,500 --> 01:30:20,027
Well, I've never really understood
what that means. I love my job.

1168
01:30:20,140 --> 01:30:22,188
I love competing. I love racing.

1169
01:30:22,380 --> 01:30:24,299
<i>Maybe you should ask Niki.</i>

1170
01:30:24,300 --> 01:30:26,659
He's the World Champion.
He's got everything to lose.

1171
01:30:26,660 --> 01:30:29,059
Mr Lauda, are you feeling pressure?

1172
01:30:29,060 --> 01:30:31,506
Do I look like I'm feeling pressure?

1173
01:30:33,580 --> 01:30:37,710
I am World Champion, and on the verge
to become World Champion again.

1174
01:30:37,820 --> 01:30:39,899
Hunt now has the opportunity to win,

1175
01:30:39,900 --> 01:30:42,059
but it's not so easy to become a champion.

1176
01:30:42,060 --> 01:30:45,189
You have to really believe it
to make it possible.

1177
01:30:45,340 --> 01:30:47,417
James, is there anything
you'd like to add?

1178
01:30:47,500 --> 01:30:51,499
If Niki is being tricky and getting
a kicky out of playing mind games...

1179
01:30:51,500 --> 01:30:53,867
...then fine, I'm flattered.

1180
01:30:53,980 --> 01:30:57,541
But the fact is, momentum is with me.
I've never felt better.

1181
01:30:57,660 --> 01:31:00,257
And I fully expect the next
press conference we will have

1182
01:31:00,340 --> 01:31:02,502
will be with me as World Champion.

1183
01:31:04,340 --> 01:31:06,859
How will you cope
with the weather, bad conditions?

1184
01:31:06,860 --> 01:31:10,419
Intermittent heavy rain
has been forecast here at Fuji today,

1185
01:31:10,420 --> 01:31:13,902
along with strong winds and occasional fog

1186
01:31:14,020 --> 01:31:15,909
rolling in from the mountain.

1187
01:31:17,700 --> 01:31:20,419
<i>And so, with today's
Japanese Grand Prix to come,</i>

1188
01:31:20,420 --> 01:31:22,259
<i>Lauda's lead a mere three points.</i>

1189
01:31:22,260 --> 01:31:23,944
<i>What a way to finish the season.</i>

1190
01:31:24,540 --> 01:31:26,099
<i>Hunt or Lauda?</i>

1191
01:31:26,100 --> 01:31:29,137
<i>Well, the final chapter will unfold when
we bring you extended coverage...</i>

1192
01:31:29,220 --> 01:31:32,339
They've got to cancel the race.
It's lethal out there.

1193
01:31:32,340 --> 01:31:34,539
The race is going ahead.

1194
01:31:34,540 --> 01:31:36,459
Television rights have been sold
all around the world.

1195
01:31:36,460 --> 01:31:39,179
The showdown between you and Niki
is all anyone wants to see.

1196
01:31:39,180 --> 01:31:42,659
With heavy rain
continuing to fall here at Fuji,

1197
01:31:42,660 --> 01:31:44,742
a decision has finally been made.

1198
01:31:44,860 --> 01:31:48,859
The 1976 Japanese Grand Prix
will go ahead.

1199
01:31:48,860 --> 01:31:51,545
<i>All drivers to your cars, please.</i>

1200
01:32:16,180 --> 01:32:17,591
<i>Five minutes to go.</i>

1201
01:33:00,780 --> 01:33:02,299
- All right?
- All right.

1202
01:33:02,300 --> 01:33:04,699
- Hold still.
- What the hell are you doing?

1203
01:33:04,700 --> 01:33:06,499
To let the condensation out.

1204
01:33:06,500 --> 01:33:09,299
- It'll also let the water in.
- Not if you're leading.

1205
01:33:09,300 --> 01:33:11,667
Trust me,
this race is all about the start.

1206
01:33:13,580 --> 01:33:16,151
- Need a hand here?
- Yeah, hold it, Teddy.

1207
01:33:30,620 --> 01:33:32,270
Okay, start the bastard.

1208
01:33:35,260 --> 01:33:36,910
Good luck, kid.

1209
01:33:38,300 --> 01:33:39,711
Good luck, James.

1210
01:34:19,260 --> 01:34:21,262
<i>Thirty seconds to go.</i>

1211
01:34:40,700 --> 01:34:42,939
<i>Electric tension here at Fuji.</i>

1212
01:34:42,940 --> 01:34:48,059
<i>80, 000 bedraggled race fans and
the racing grudge match of the decade.</i>

1213
01:34:48,060 --> 01:34:50,259
<i>And there's Mario Andretti
in pole position,</i>

1214
01:34:50,260 --> 01:34:52,262
<i>James Hunt alongside him.</i>

1215
01:34:54,420 --> 01:34:56,419
<i>On Row 2 of the grid,</i>

1216
01:34:56,420 --> 01:34:58,379
<i>there is Niki Lauda,</i>

1217
01:34:58,380 --> 01:35:00,899
<i>and on Row 3 of the grid,
Jody Scheckter from South Africa</i>

1218
01:35:00,900 --> 01:35:02,419
<i>in the six-wheel Tyrrell.</i>

1219
01:35:02,420 --> 01:35:04,502
<i>Behind him, the rest of the 25-car field.</i>

1220
01:35:22,340 --> 01:35:26,345
There's the flag, and finally
the Japanese Grand Prix is underway!

1221
01:35:38,580 --> 01:35:41,819
<i>In these conditions,
it must be almost impossible to drive</i>

1222
01:35:41,820 --> 01:35:43,822
<i>a 450-horsepower car.</i>

1223
01:36:10,980 --> 01:36:14,059
<i>And it's Andretti who has the lead,
but Hunt is attacking.</i>

1224
01:36:14,060 --> 01:36:17,099
<i>Hunt's going round
the outside of Andretti.</i>

1225
01:36:17,100 --> 01:36:18,739
<i>Niki Lauda following him through.</i>

1226
01:36:18,740 --> 01:36:21,505
<i>Hunt leads into the first right-hander.</i>

1227
01:37:04,035 --> 01:37:06,379
<i>Hunt comes through
to complete his first lap,</i>

1228
01:37:06,380 --> 01:37:07,859
<i>leading the field.</i>

1229
01:37:07,860 --> 01:37:10,017
<i>At least he has clear vision
in front of him.</i>

1230
01:37:10,100 --> 01:37:12,262
<i>Niki Lauda, behind him, eating his spray.</i>

1231
01:37:31,740 --> 01:37:33,219
<i>Lauda is slowing.</i>

1232
01:37:33,220 --> 01:37:36,179
<i>Niki Lauda is bringing
the Ferrari number one into the pit.</i>

1233
01:37:37,860 --> 01:37:41,110
<i>Some sort of problem, we can't
imagine what, so early in the race.</i>

1234
01:37:47,380 --> 01:37:50,827
What's wrong with the car?
What's wrong with the car?

1235
01:37:51,980 --> 01:37:53,709
Niki, what's wrong with the car?

1236
01:37:54,060 --> 01:37:56,142
Nothing. Car's perfect.

1237
01:38:00,540 --> 01:38:02,979
- What are you doing?
- I'm stopping.

1238
01:38:02,980 --> 01:38:05,219
<i>His mechanics
are asking what the problem is.</i>

1239
01:38:05,220 --> 01:38:07,541
<i>But wait!
Niki Lauda's getting out of the car!</i>

1240
01:38:07,660 --> 01:38:09,339
This is sensational!

1241
01:38:09,340 --> 01:38:12,340
The reigning World Champion,
Niki Lauda, is out of this race.

1242
01:38:13,180 --> 01:38:14,939
It's too dangerous.

1243
01:38:14,940 --> 01:38:18,540
Niki, you want me to say there was
a problem with the car, for the media?

1244
01:38:19,460 --> 01:38:20,950
No.

1245
01:38:21,340 --> 01:38:22,751
Tell them the truth.

1246
01:38:23,620 --> 01:38:25,190
<i>Now, what is happening?</i>

1247
01:38:25,300 --> 01:38:29,225
<i>They're talking to the team manager.
Lauda explaining something.</i>

1248
01:38:44,780 --> 01:38:48,139
<i>With Lauda out, James Hunt
knows he has to finish this race</i>

1249
01:38:48,140 --> 01:38:51,979
<i>in third place or higher
to be World Champion.</i>

1250
01:38:51,980 --> 01:38:54,739
<i>But the job's not done yet for James Hunt.</i>

1251
01:38:54,740 --> 01:38:59,348
<i>In these dreadful conditions,
he still has to go the distance.</i>

1252
01:39:00,460 --> 01:39:02,303
<i>Fifteen laps to go here at Fuji.</i>

1253
01:39:02,420 --> 01:39:04,579
<i>James Hunt or Niki Lauda?</i>

1254
01:39:04,580 --> 01:39:07,739
<i>This extraordinary season is not over yet.</i>

1255
01:39:07,740 --> 01:39:11,187
<i>In this treacherous final round,
can James Hunt hang on?</i>

1256
01:39:11,700 --> 01:39:13,619
<i>And the scoreboard tells a story.</i>

1257
01:39:13,620 --> 01:39:16,430
<i>Lap 58. Hunt in the lead.</i>

1258
01:39:18,420 --> 01:39:20,370
Oh, God, his tyres, they're blistering.

1259
01:39:21,675 --> 01:39:23,739
<i>Brambilla very close behind now,</i>

1260
01:39:23,740 --> 01:39:25,708
<i>closing on him all the time now.</i>

1261
01:39:25,820 --> 01:39:29,059
<i>And he's trying to drive
inside James Hunt.</i>

1262
01:39:29,060 --> 01:39:31,586
<i>Hunt cuts across the orange March nose.</i>

1263
01:39:31,700 --> 01:39:34,059
<i>Hunt's not having that at all.
And he's spinning.</i>

1264
01:39:34,060 --> 01:39:37,299
<i>He missed Hunt there, but almost
took James Hunt out of the race</i>

1265
01:39:37,300 --> 01:39:39,739
<i>and out of the world championship.</i>

1266
01:39:39,740 --> 01:39:42,471
<i>Now we find Mario Andretti
closing on James Hunt.</i>

1267
01:39:47,020 --> 01:39:48,988
<i>Mario Andretti's going past Hunt!</i>

1268
01:39:49,460 --> 01:39:52,464
<i>Hunt is slowing. James Hunt
seems to have a problem.</i>

1269
01:39:58,300 --> 01:40:00,139
<i>Despite these wet conditions,</i>

1270
01:40:00,140 --> 01:40:01,897
<i>these wet-weather tyres
do wear extremely fast.</i>

1271
01:40:01,980 --> 01:40:04,108
Hunt's tyres, they've gone.

1272
01:40:04,340 --> 01:40:08,026
<i>Hunt nursing his car back to the pit stop.</i>

1273
01:40:10,020 --> 01:40:12,068
<i>That back marker's going past Hunt.</i>

1274
01:40:24,500 --> 01:40:27,259
<i>Look at that left front tyre...
Right front tyre, sorry.</i>

1275
01:40:27,260 --> 01:40:30,423
<i>No tread on it at all.
And the other one is flat.</i>

1276
01:40:30,580 --> 01:40:32,708
Let's go! Let's go!

1277
01:40:37,260 --> 01:40:39,739
Okay? When did you break
your gear lever?

1278
01:40:39,740 --> 01:40:41,419
Nine or ten laps ago.

1279
01:40:41,420 --> 01:40:43,866
- Alastair, we need to lift it.
- Come on!

1280
01:40:43,980 --> 01:40:45,739
- At the front.
- Let's go.

1281
01:40:45,740 --> 01:40:49,019
<i>Regazzoni's Ferrari
and Jacques Lafitte in the Ligier</i>

1282
01:40:49,020 --> 01:40:50,670
have gone ahead.

1283
01:40:50,780 --> 01:40:52,459
Come on, hurry!

1284
01:40:52,460 --> 01:40:55,579
You did it.
You're going to be World Champion!

1285
01:40:55,580 --> 01:40:57,099
Not yet.

1286
01:40:57,100 --> 01:41:00,939
<i>A few laps ago, James Hunt
was looking like champion elect.</i>

1287
01:41:00,940 --> 01:41:03,440
<i>Now it looks as though
it's all gone wrong for him.</i>

1288
01:41:04,740 --> 01:41:06,219
- James.
- Come on!

1289
01:41:06,220 --> 01:41:07,739
- Listen.
- What?

1290
01:41:07,740 --> 01:41:10,059
Just go easy out there.

1291
01:41:10,060 --> 01:41:14,099
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying look after yourself.

1292
01:41:14,100 --> 01:41:16,059
We want you back in one piece.

1293
01:41:16,060 --> 01:41:19,499
You're too far back. There's
too many drivers in front of you.

1294
01:41:19,500 --> 01:41:23,505
- There's always next year.
- So that's it? It's over?

1295
01:41:23,900 --> 01:41:25,459
Clear!

1296
01:41:25,460 --> 01:41:26,985
James.

1297
01:41:28,660 --> 01:41:30,583
- Clear!
- Fuck it!

1298
01:41:34,500 --> 01:41:37,819
James Hunt rejoins the race
in sixth position.

1299
01:41:37,820 --> 01:41:41,711
<i>There are four laps left to go.
Surely no way back for the Brit now.</i>

1300
01:42:01,580 --> 01:42:02,914
Concentrate, Superstar.

1301
01:42:02,915 --> 01:42:04,819
<i>Just brings it back under control.</i>

1302
01:42:04,820 --> 01:42:06,099
<i>Sliding the McLaren</i>

1303
01:42:06,100 --> 01:42:07,340
<i>on the very edge there.</i>

1304
01:42:09,260 --> 01:42:10,546
<i>Hunt's M23</i>

1305
01:42:10,660 --> 01:42:12,339
<i>twitching this way and that under braking.</i>

1306
01:42:12,340 --> 01:42:13,777
And he almost loses it right there.

1307
01:42:13,860 --> 01:42:16,581
<i>Hunt on the tail
of Jacques Lafitte in the blue Ligier.</i>

1308
01:42:24,540 --> 01:42:25,951
Oh, don't do it, James.

1309
01:42:29,075 --> 01:42:31,019
<i>He's inches away from the pit wall.</i>

1310
01:42:31,020 --> 01:42:32,829
<i>He's inches away from the Ligier.</i>

1311
01:42:41,860 --> 01:42:44,339
<i>James Hunt has made up another place,</i>

1312
01:42:44,340 --> 01:42:45,419
<i>but it's not enough,</i>

1313
01:42:45,420 --> 01:42:46,870
<i>and this race is running out.</i>

1314
01:42:55,700 --> 01:42:57,702
<i>And Watson has spun.
Watson has spun.</i>

1315
01:43:02,340 --> 01:43:05,179
<i>Hunt manages to weave his way
between that back marker</i>

1316
01:43:05,180 --> 01:43:07,259
<i>and the stationary Penske.</i>

1317
01:43:07,260 --> 01:43:09,339
He's catching Regazzoni

1318
01:43:09,340 --> 01:43:11,059
but, in these conditions,
it's one thing to catch up,

1319
01:43:11,060 --> 01:43:13,267
it's quite another to overtake.

1320
01:43:16,660 --> 01:43:20,790
<i>He's alongside Clay Regazzoni.
This could be the world championship.</i>

1321
01:43:29,220 --> 01:43:30,745
<i>He's got him!</i>

1322
01:43:31,207 --> 01:43:34,247
The scoreboard
still shows Hunt in 5th place.

1323
01:43:46,020 --> 01:43:48,179
<i>Hunt crosses the line.</i>

1324
01:43:48,180 --> 01:43:51,859
<i>Now, he needed to finish third to score
enough points to be World Champion,</i>

1325
01:43:51,860 --> 01:43:56,459
<i>and in the confusion here, we're being
told that he may have finished fifth.</i>

1326
01:43:56,460 --> 01:43:58,659
He finished fifth?

1327
01:43:58,660 --> 01:44:01,539
<i>Our lap charts show Hunt in third place.</i>

1328
01:44:01,540 --> 01:44:03,539
<i>Well, if the scoreboard's right,</i>

1329
01:44:03,540 --> 01:44:06,139
<i>it means he's just missed out
on the championship.</i>

1330
01:44:06,140 --> 01:44:09,781
<i>Crushing defeat for Hunt
after such a heroic drive.</i>

1331
01:44:13,740 --> 01:44:16,339
I can see the race stewards conferring,

1332
01:44:16,340 --> 01:44:18,059
examining the official lap charts.

1333
01:44:18,060 --> 01:44:20,810
<i>We're just going to have to wait
for their verdict here.</i>

1334
01:44:38,075 --> 01:44:39,739
Let's get you out of there, buddy.

1335
01:44:39,740 --> 01:44:41,899
I'm sorry, Teddy. I'm sorry.
I thought I could make up the ground.

1336
01:44:41,900 --> 01:44:44,059
Sorry? What are you talking about?
You did it.

1337
01:44:44,060 --> 01:44:46,899
- Did what?
- Jesus. You crazy bastard.

1338
01:44:46,900 --> 01:44:50,109
You came third. You got the points.
You're champion of the world!

1339
01:44:50,620 --> 01:44:53,863
<i>James Hunt is now officially confirmed</i>

1340
01:44:53,980 --> 01:44:56,028
<i>as finishing third here in Japan,</i>

1341
01:44:56,660 --> 01:45:00,379
<i>and that means
he is champion of the world.</i>

1342
01:45:01,780 --> 01:45:07,139
<i>Our new World Champion,
James Hunt, by just one single point.</i>

1343
01:45:12,260 --> 01:45:13,750
<i>Did we really win?</i>

1344
01:45:17,820 --> 01:45:20,061
World bloody Champion!

1345
01:45:28,755 --> 01:45:30,819
Tell us, James,
what are you going to do now?

1346
01:45:30,820 --> 01:45:32,982
I shall be getting drunk.

1347
01:45:33,500 --> 01:45:36,299
It's wonderful, an absolute dream...

1348
01:45:49,380 --> 01:45:51,064
Are you okay?

1349
01:45:53,177 --> 01:45:54,767
Fine.

1350
01:45:56,387 --> 01:45:58,137
No regrets.

1351
01:46:01,397 --> 01:46:03,227
Not one.

1352
01:46:23,220 --> 01:46:25,299
<i>And our special guest,</i>

1353
01:46:25,300 --> 01:46:27,143
<i>Formula 1 champion James Hunt.</i>

1354
01:46:50,540 --> 01:46:52,622
Wait. Come on.

1355
01:46:55,780 --> 01:46:57,339
<i>There's no better motor oil</i>

1356
01:46:57,340 --> 01:46:58,944
<i>than Havoline.</i>

1357
01:47:09,460 --> 01:47:11,459
Yes, me, too.
Where are we going?

1358
01:47:11,460 --> 01:47:12,994
Anywhere I want to go.

1359
01:47:12,995 --> 01:47:15,339
And I don't have to hijack it, either.

1360
01:47:15,340 --> 01:47:17,059
As long as I pay for it.

1361
01:47:17,060 --> 01:47:19,381
I'm starving.
Let's get some food.

1362
01:47:30,195 --> 01:47:32,299
- Where are we going?
- You lot go ahead.

1363
01:47:32,300 --> 01:47:34,268
I won't be a minute.

1364
01:47:40,180 --> 01:47:41,784
Good to see you.

1365
01:47:45,860 --> 01:47:48,577
I heard you were spending
more and more time in one of these.

1366
01:47:48,660 --> 01:47:50,628
Do you fly?
No.

1367
01:47:51,020 --> 01:47:52,570
I don't think they'd insure me.

1368
01:47:52,660 --> 01:47:54,617
You should try.
It's good for discipline.

1369
01:47:54,700 --> 01:47:57,217
You have to stay within the rules,
stick to regulations,

1370
01:47:57,300 --> 01:47:59,871
suppress the ego.
It helps with the racing.

1371
01:47:59,980 --> 01:48:03,019
And there I was thinking
you were about to wax lyrical

1372
01:48:03,020 --> 01:48:04,624
about the romance of flight.

1373
01:48:04,980 --> 01:48:06,550
No, that's all bullshit.

1374
01:48:07,700 --> 01:48:09,145
So, what brings you here?

1375
01:48:10,300 --> 01:48:12,859
A friend's wedding.
At least I think it was a wedding.

1376
01:48:12,860 --> 01:48:15,779
Might have been a birthday or something.
It's all a bit of a blur.

1377
01:48:15,780 --> 01:48:17,099
How about you? Have you been at Fiorano?

1378
01:48:17,100 --> 01:48:18,261
Pre-season testing.

1379
01:48:18,380 --> 01:48:20,379
- You're relentless.
- Thank you.

1380
01:48:20,380 --> 01:48:22,619
I'm not sure that was meant
as a compliment.

1381
01:48:22,620 --> 01:48:24,939
When do you start testing? Next week?

1382
01:48:24,940 --> 01:48:26,979
No. What, are you nuts?

1383
01:48:26,980 --> 01:48:28,779
I didn't just win
the biggest thing of my life

1384
01:48:28,780 --> 01:48:30,480
so I could get right back to work.

1385
01:48:31,540 --> 01:48:34,225
Why? You have to.

1386
01:48:34,540 --> 01:48:37,979
To prove to all the people who will
always say you just won it because...

1387
01:48:37,980 --> 01:48:41,382
Because of what?
Because of your accident?

1388
01:48:42,900 --> 01:48:45,000
Niki, is that other people,
or is that you?

1389
01:48:45,580 --> 01:48:48,739
I won, okay? On the all-important day,
when it came down to it,

1390
01:48:48,740 --> 01:48:51,659
we raced on equal terms,
equally good cars.

1391
01:48:51,660 --> 01:48:53,899
And I put my life on the line,
and I saw it through.

1392
01:48:53,900 --> 01:48:55,948
- And you call that winning?
- Yes.

1393
01:48:56,060 --> 01:48:58,142
The risks were totally unacceptable.

1394
01:48:58,660 --> 01:49:01,140
You were prepared to die.
To me, that's losing.

1395
01:49:01,260 --> 01:49:02,899
Yes, I was. I admit it.

1396
01:49:02,900 --> 01:49:05,779
I was prepared to die
to beat you that day.

1397
01:49:05,780 --> 01:49:08,777
And that's the effect you have on me.
You'd pushed me that far.

1398
01:49:08,860 --> 01:49:10,271
And it felt great.

1399
01:49:11,180 --> 01:49:13,579
I mean, hell,
isn't that what we're in this for?

1400
01:49:13,580 --> 01:49:16,948
To stare death in the face
and to cheat it?

1401
01:49:17,300 --> 01:49:21,100
Come on, there's nobility in that.
It's... It's like being knights.

1402
01:49:22,100 --> 01:49:23,864
You English, you're such assholes.

1403
01:49:24,820 --> 01:49:26,265
You know my position.

1404
01:49:26,540 --> 01:49:28,019
Twenty per cent risk.

1405
01:49:28,020 --> 01:49:31,819
No, no, no, Niki, don't bring the
percentages into this. Don't be a pro.

1406
01:49:31,820 --> 01:49:34,570
The minute you do that,
you kill what's good about this.

1407
01:49:34,780 --> 01:49:36,544
You kill the sport.

1408
01:49:39,660 --> 01:49:41,310
James!

1409
01:49:41,620 --> 01:49:43,463
- James!
- Come on!

1410
01:49:46,460 --> 01:49:47,825
I've got to go.

1411
01:49:49,340 --> 01:49:51,308
Careful in this thing.

1412
01:49:52,340 --> 01:49:53,830
James.

1413
01:49:59,060 --> 01:50:02,826
You know, in hospital, the toughest part
of my treatment was the vacuum.

1414
01:50:03,140 --> 01:50:06,064
Pumping the shit out of my lungs.
It was hell.

1415
01:50:07,140 --> 01:50:09,390
And while doing it,
I was watching television.

1416
01:50:09,660 --> 01:50:12,499
- You winning all my points.
- Your points?

1417
01:50:12,500 --> 01:50:15,050
"That bastard Hunt," I would say.
"I hate that guy."

1418
01:50:15,260 --> 01:50:17,419
And then one day the doctor came and said,

1419
01:50:17,420 --> 01:50:19,707
"Mr Lauda,
may I offer a piece of advice?"

1420
01:50:19,820 --> 01:50:23,579
"Stop thinking of it as a curse to
have been given an enemy in life."

1421
01:50:23,580 --> 01:50:25,819
"It can be a blessing, too."

1422
01:50:25,820 --> 01:50:29,137
"A wise man gets more from his enemies
than a fool from his friends."

1423
01:50:29,220 --> 01:50:31,507
And you know what? He was right.

1424
01:50:34,100 --> 01:50:37,899
Look at us. We were both
a pair of kids when we met.

1425
01:50:37,900 --> 01:50:39,739
Hot-headed jerks in Formula 3.

1426
01:50:39,740 --> 01:50:41,583
Disowned by our families.

1427
01:50:41,700 --> 01:50:43,065
Headed nowhere.

1428
01:50:44,180 --> 01:50:46,539
And now we're both champions of the world.

1429
01:50:46,540 --> 01:50:47,951
It was not bad, huh?

1430
01:50:49,020 --> 01:50:51,019
No, it's not bad.

1431
01:50:51,020 --> 01:50:54,581
So, don't let me down now.
I need you busting my balls.

1432
01:50:55,020 --> 01:50:57,785
- Get back to work.
- I will, Niki, I will.

1433
01:50:58,540 --> 01:51:00,588
But I intend to enjoy myself first.

1434
01:51:00,940 --> 01:51:03,261
Some of life needs to be for pleasure.

1435
01:51:03,380 --> 01:51:06,779
What's the point of having
a million cups and medals and planes

1436
01:51:06,780 --> 01:51:08,942
if you don't have any fun?

1437
01:51:09,740 --> 01:51:11,469
How is that winning?

1438
01:51:12,540 --> 01:51:15,271
- James!
- We're gonna leave without you!

1439
01:51:15,780 --> 01:51:17,225
James!

1440
01:51:21,060 --> 01:51:22,660
I'll see you on race day, champ.

1441
01:51:24,220 --> 01:51:26,382
You will... champ.

1442
01:51:28,900 --> 01:51:30,664
You look good, Niki.

1443
01:51:31,220 --> 01:51:34,420
The only guy to have his face burnt off
and it be an improvement.

1444
01:51:40,940 --> 01:51:43,059
<i>Of course, he didn't listen to me.</i>

1445
01:51:43,060 --> 01:51:44,579
<i>For James,</i>

1446
01:51:44,580 --> 01:51:46,779
<i>one world title was enough.</i>

1447
01:51:46,780 --> 01:51:48,299
<i>He had proved</i>

1448
01:51:48,300 --> 01:51:51,659
<i>what he needed to prove, to himself</i>

1449
01:51:51,660 --> 01:51:53,947
<i>and anyone who doubted him.</i>

1450
01:51:54,780 --> 01:51:56,669
<i>And two years later he retired.</i>

1451
01:51:56,940 --> 01:52:00,581
<i>When I saw him next in London
seven years later,</i>

1452
01:52:00,700 --> 01:52:02,828
<i>me as champion again,</i>

1453
01:52:02,940 --> 01:52:04,899
<i>him as broadcaster,</i>

1454
01:52:04,900 --> 01:52:09,303
<i>he was barefoot
on a bicycle with a flat tyre.</i>

1455
01:52:09,420 --> 01:52:12,264
<i>Still living each day like his last.</i>

1456
01:52:14,020 --> 01:52:15,510
<i>When I heard he'd died,</i>

1457
01:52:15,620 --> 01:52:17,987
<i>aged 45, of a heart attack,</i>

1458
01:52:18,100 --> 01:52:19,625
<i>I wasn't surprised.</i>

1459
01:52:20,620 --> 01:52:22,509
<i>I was just sad.</i>

1460
01:52:23,860 --> 01:52:25,779
<i>People always think of us as rivals,</i>

1461
01:52:25,780 --> 01:52:29,387
<i>but he was among the very few I liked,</i>

1462
01:52:30,700 --> 01:52:33,670
<i>and even fewer that I respected.</i>

1463
01:52:36,820 --> 01:52:39,551
<i>He remains the only person I envied.</i>

1464
